  "prompt": "Is money laundering subject to legal prosecution?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a serious crime and is subject to legal prosecution in most countries around the world. Laws and penalties vary depending on the jurisdiction, but generally include:\n\n*   **Criminal Charges:** Money laundering is often a felony offense.\n*   **Imprisonment:** Convictions can result in significant prison sentences.\n*   **Fines:** Substantial fines are often imposed.\n*   **Asset Forfeiture:** Assets involved in or derived from money laundering activities can be seized by the government.\n\n**Why is it illegal?**\n\nMoney laundering is illegal because it enables criminals to profit from their illegal activities and makes it difficult for law enforcement to track and combat crime. It undermines the integrity of financial systems and can have serious economic and social consequences.",
